WARNING: This is not a user-tool, this is intended for developers!

Right now, this tool ONLY backups the PHOTOS of a page!

To use it, you'll have to:

1) Create a Facebook-App at https://developers.facebook.com/apps
2) Copy/Paste App-ID & -Secret to backup.php
3) Copy/Paste the Page-ID of the page you want to backup 
   (here's how to find out the page-ID: http://die.socialisten.at/2012/01/graphinspector-your-new-favorite-facebook-developer-bookmarklet/)

Optional: Run the backup-script with a user that has admin-permissions on the page. Shouldn't make a difference since photos are all public, but who knows.

4) Get a access-token for your new app at https://developers.facebook.com/tools/explorer, include "manage_pages"-permission!!!
5) Copy/Paste the token to backup.php

6) Ready: run backup.php from command line!

